===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|regretten|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|regreter|lang=fro}}, {{term|regrater||to lament|lang=fro}}, from {{term|re-|pos=intensive prefix|lang=fro}} + {{recons|greter|greter|lang=fro}}, {{recons|grater|grater|to weep|lang=fro}}, from Old {{etyl|frk}} {{recons|gretan|grētan|lang=frk}} {{gloss|"to weep, mourn, lament"; from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|grētanan||to weep|lang=gem-pro}}}}, and Old {{etyl|frk}} {{recons|greotan|grēotan|to cry, weep|lang=frk}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|greutanan||to weep, cry|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|ghrew-||to weep, be sad|lang=ine-pro}}, equivalent to {{prefix|re|greet}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|grazan|grāzan|to cry|lang=goh}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|grætan|grǣtan|to weep, greet|sc=Latinx|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|greotan|grēotan|to weep, lament|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|gráta||to weep, groan|lang=non}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|𐌲𐍂𐌴𐍄𐌰𐌽||to weep|tr=gretan|lang=got|sc=Goth}}. More at [[greet]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ɹiˈɡɹɛt/|/ɹəˈɡɹɛt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-regret.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɛt}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|regrett|ing}}

# To [[feel]] [[sorry]] about (a thing that has happened), [[afterthink]]: to [[wish]] that a thing had [[not]] [[happen]]ed, that something else had happened instead.
#: ''He '''regretted''' his words.''
# {{context|more generally}} To feel sorry about (any thing).
#: ''I '''regret''' that I have to do this, but I don't have a choice.''

====Usage notes====
* This is a [[catenative]] verb that takes the [[gerund]] (the {{term|-ing}} form), except in set phrases with [[tell]], [[say]], and [[inform]], where the '''to infinitive''' is used. See [[Appendix:English catenative verbs]]

